, DNA/BOLD ID RDOPO084-09, GenBank GU669596, DNA/BOLD ID RDOPO085-09, GenBank GU669597, (CCDB, USNM). Sandoval Co: Pakitza Campground, 4 mi. E. Ponderosa, Santa. Fe Nat. Forest: 7 ♂, 9 ♀, em. 4-11 Aug 1969, D. &amp; M. Davis, DRD 642.1,Host: 
<taxonomicName id="38E0F23ADB4FF65D060BC5039A10C2F0" class="Trematoda" family="Hemiuridae" genus="Robinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Robinia neomexicana" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="24" pageNumber="53" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="neomexicana">Robinia neomexicana</taxonomicName>
, slides USNM 34183, 34184, (USNM).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7EF8F8CAB69CB09ABDE4BEF10CE941F8" pageId="24" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2944D7B4D05AC914EF4425E78A81A009" pageId="24" pageNumber="53">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33AB3EDEFE9A01810C88C21B2AB74A18" pageId="24" pageNumber="53">Known only from the southwestern United States from Arizona and New Mexico.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CD537968F6F2B510AB71DF5F222ED7D9" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="24" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7A42AF98A3293964181F90F903F2633F" pageId="24" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="28FABFDE3510B3E4E685DB14F4D00AD5" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="24" pageNumber="53">
The specific name is derived from the specific name of its plant host. The specific epithet is an adjective in the nominative singular
<pageBreakToken id="21079BE82E9D205807524EB9A55EFBEF" pageId="25" pageNumber="54" start="start">.</pageBreakToken>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
